ROUND 10 FEATURE MATCH: ELIAS WATSFELDT VS. (22) ALEXANDER HAYNE
================================================================



 Posted in [GRAND PRIX MILAN 2015](/en/events/coverage/gpmil15)
 on December 14, 2014 






![](https://media.magic.wizards.com/styles/auth_small/public/images/person/henke_author.jpg)
By Tobi Henke










With four Grand Prix Top 8s to his name, Sweden's Elias Watsfeldt was still no match for Canada's Alexander Hayne. At least not when comparing their career stats. Currently ranked No. 22, Hayne could boast a whopping three Grand Prix wins out of five Top 8s with a Pro Tour victory to boot!


![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)



Watsfeldt was playing Red-Green-White Zoo, an old favorite that had fallen out of favor in modern Modern times but was currently experiencing something similar to a small comeback. Hayne, on the other hand, was running three-color [Jeskai Ascendancy](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Jeskai+Ascendancy), one of the newest and most popular creations of the format.



**Game 1**



As Zoo players are wont to do, Watsfeldt started aggressive with [Loam Lion](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Loam+Lion) and [Tarmogoyf](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Tarmogoyf). He then saved the Lion from [Lightning Bolt](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lightning+Bolt) via [Mutagenic Growth](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mutagenic+Growth) and added another [Loam Lion](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Loam+Lion) to his team.


![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)



Meanwhileapart from one [Gitaxian Probe](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Gitaxian+Probe) and the previously mentioned [Lightning Bolt](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lightning+Bolt)Hayne had cast nothing on his first three turns. Now he summoned [Fatestitcher](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Fatestitcher). Watsfeldt had a [Lightning Bolt](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lightning+Bolt) of his own and that was it.



Elias Watsfeldt 1-0 (22) Alexander Hayne



"Let's try that again," said Hayne as he presented his deck. "I'm playing first."



**Game 2**



Once again Watsfeldt led with [Loam Lion](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Loam+Lion) and once again he used [Mutagenic Growth](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mutagenic+Growth) to save it from death by [Lightning Bolt](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lightning+Bolt). Watsfeldt had no follow-up play, however, while Hayne dug deeper and deeper into his library with [Serum Visions](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Serum+Visions), [Thought Scour](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Thought+Scour), [Dig Through Time](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Dig+Through+Time), and [Izzet Charm](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Izzet+Charm). Another [Lightning Bolt](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lightning+Bolt) killed the [Loam Lion](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Loam+Lion) after all, but Watsfeldt replaced it with [Ghor-Clan Rampager](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ghor-Clan+Rampager) and [Tarmogoyf](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Tarmogoyf), speeding up the clock considerably.



By now, Hayne had placed both Elesh Norn, Grand Cenobite and [Unburial Rites](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Unburial+Rites) in his graveyard and cast the latter targeting the former. Time for Watsfeldt's super secret sideboard tech! He exiled the Phyrexian's Grand Cenobite using the Phyrexian's own Surgical [Extraction](http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Extraction). He began looking through Hayne's libraryno more Elesh Norn there, of course, but still some information to be gleaneduntil the players did the math and found that Hayne would simply be dead on Watsfeldt's next attack.



"Now that was quick."



Elias Watsfeldt 2-0 (22) Alexander Hayne
